{
  "text": "The surgical procedures were based on previous experiments [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . At 27-28 days of age, rats were anesthetized with 0.08 ml/100 g (s.c.) of Hypnorm (Janssen, Belgium) and positioned in a stereotaxic apparatus (David Kopf, USA). Guide cannulae (24 gauge; Cooper's Needleworks, UK) were implanted bilaterally. The cannulae were aimed 0.5 mm above the PrL (coordinates: anteriorposterior (AP) \u00fe 2.6 mm from Bregma; medial-lateral (ML) \u00b1 0.8 mm from the midline; dorsal-ventral (DV) \u00c0 3.2 mm from skull surface), the IL (coordinates: AP \u00fe 2.6 mm; ML \u00b1 0.8 mm; DV \u00c0 4.1 mm), the medial/ventral OFC (MO/VO; coordinates: AP \u00fe 3.3 mm; ML \u00b1 0.8 mm; DV \u00c0 5.3 mm), the dorsomedial striatum (DMS; coordinates: AP \u00fe 1.5 mm; ML \u00b11.9 mm; DV \u00c0 5.1 mm), the NAcc core (coordinates: AP, \u00fe 1.5 mm; ML \u00b1 1.9 mm; DV \u00c0 6.5 mm), or 1.0 mm above the NAcc shell (coordinates: AP \u00fe 1.5 mm; ML \u00b10.8 mm; DV \u00c0 5.3 mm). Coordinates were based on previous experiments [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] or determined by pilot placements in 4-week-old rats.",
  "correct_citation": {
